Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended approach):

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Simulate async fetch
        await Task.Delay(500);
        Name = "Widget Pro";
        Price = 29.99m;
        IsAvailable = true;
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` notifications) and a `LoadCommand` automatically.

**XAML usage** — set `x:DataType` at the page root for compiled bindings:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel">
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <vm:ProductDetailViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="16" Spacing="8">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='In Stock: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**
- `[ObservableProperty]` on a field generates the public property + change notification
- `[RelayCommand]` on `LoadAsync` generates `LoadCommand` (with built-in `IsRunning`/can-execute handling)
- `x:DataType` enables compiled bindings (8–20× faster, AOT-safe)
- Add `<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>` to your `.csproj` to catch binding errors at build time

NuGet package: `CommunityToolkit.Mvvm` (≥ 8.0).
